SUMMARY:Art Outdoors: Insect Friends
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we explore art outdoors\, mixing natural materials with traditional art disciplines\, testing new nature-based art techniques\, and using inspiration from nature to create artistic masterpieces. \nEach day will feature a different outdoor art activity – today’s activity is making insect friends! Join us as we use natural materials to decorate various bug buddies. \nThis drop-in program is designed for kids ages 7 and under and occurs outdoors from 10:30 am – 11:30 am at the picnic tables below the Nature PlaySpace. All children must be accompanied by an adult. Come dressed for the weather and prepared to get messy!
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/art-outdoors-insect-friends-2/
LOCATION:Prairie Ridge\, 1671 Gold Star Drive\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
CATEGORIES:Children,Outdoor Experiences,Walk-up Programs
